==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Polypus
<hw>Pol"y*pus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it> E.
<plw>Polypuses</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>, L. <plw>Polypi</plw>
<pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. See <er>Polyp</er>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>Same as <er>Polyp</er>.</def><-- polyp is the
normal term now -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A tumor, usually with a narrow
base, somewhat resembling a pear, -- found in the nose, uterus, etc.,
and produced by hypertrophy of some portion of the mucous
membrane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polyrhizous</ent>⟦br⟧
